TID_SHOTGUN_GIRL_DESC.EN: Shelly's spread-fire shotgun blasts the other team with buckshot. Her Super destroys cover and keeps her opponents at a distance!

TID_LONG_RANGE_SHOTGUN_DESC.EN: Shelly's boomstick fires a wide spread of pellets to a medium range. The more pellets hit, the greater the damage.

TID_MEGA_BLASH_ULTI_DESC.EN: Shelly's Super Shell obliterates both cover and enemies. Any survivors get knocked back.

TID_GUNSLINGER_DESC.EN: An unlikely hero that often finds himself in the wrong place at the right time. He's not one to shy away from a mirror and is simply brimming with confidence!

TID_RAPID_FIRE_DESC.EN: Colt shoots six straight long-range shots out of his revolvers.

TID_RAPID_FIRE_ULTI_DESC.EN: Colt rattles off a massive burst of bullets that shoot extra far and destroy cover.

TID_BULL_DUDE_DESC.EN: Bull deals massive damage up close with his shotgun. For his Super move, he charges through barriers and knocks back enemies!

TID_SHOTGUN_BLAST_DESC.EN: Bull's double-barreled shotgun deals heavy damage. It has very short range, so Bull likes to get up close and personal.

TID_CHARGE_DESC.EN: Bull puts his head down and bulldozes through opponents and obstacles. He's always been headstrong!

TID_ROCKET_GIRL_DESC.EN: When Brock's not lighting up the battle with rockets, he's lighting up the dance floor with his smooth moves.

TID_FIREWORKS_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Brock lets fly with a single Rockin' Rocket that really goes the distance.

TID_FIREWORKS_ULTI_DESC.EN: Brock fires a rocket barrage that takes out enemies and obstacles. He only wants to see you bathing in the Rocket Rain!

TID_TNT_DUDE_DESC.EN: Long thought lost deep down a mine. Mad Dynamike is back - and he's still itching to blow everything to smithereens!

TID_MORTAR_DESC.EN: Mike tosses two sticks of dynamite, passing over any obstacles in the way. The fuses are cut as short as Mike's explosive temper!

TID_MORTAR_ULTI_DESC.EN: A big-bada-barrel of dynamite blows up cover. Any surviving enemies get knocked back on impact!

TID_LUCHADOR_DESC.EN: El Primo throws a flurry of punches at his enemies. His Super is a leaping elbow drop that deals damage to all caught underneath!

TID_LUCHADOR_WEAPON_DESC.EN: El Primo fires off a furious flurry of four fiery fists. That's a spicy jalapeno knuckle sandwich!

TID_LUCHADOR_ULTI_DESC.EN: Leaping high, El Primo drops an Intergalactic Elbow that knocks around enemies and destroys cover!

TID_TRICKSHOT_DUDE_DESC.EN: Rico fires a burst of bullets that bounce off walls. His Super burst is a long barrage of bouncy bullets that pierce targets!

TID_TRICKSHOT_DUDE_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Rico's bullets bounce off walls, gaining range. They can hit enemies behind cover.

TID_TRICKSHOT_DUDE_ULTI_DESC.EN: Rico fires a long burst of bullets that pierce through enemies and bounce off walls, gaining range.

TID_CACTUS_DESC.EN: Spike throws cactus grenades that send needles flying, and a show-stopping Super: a field of cactus spines that slows down and damages enemies!

TID_CACTUS_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Spike fires off a small cactus that explodes, shooting spikes in different directions.

TID_CACTUS_ULTI_DESC.EN: Spike lobs a thorny grenade. Enemies caught in the blast area take damage and are slowed down.

TID_BARKEEP_DESC.EN: Barley serves the finest beverages in Starr Park. But dirty his bar up and steam comes out and bottles start flying!

TID_BARKEEP_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Barley lobs a bottle, breaking it on the ground. Enemies take damage from the splash, and more damage over time if they stay in the puddle.

TID_BARKEEP_ULTI_DESC.EN: Barley hurls a flurry of fiery bottles, covering a huge area in flames. This one's on the house!

TID_MECHANIC_DESC.EN: Jessie's Shock Rifle shoots energy orbs that bounce between enemies. Her Super deploys a cute but deadly gun turret!

TID_MECHANIC_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Jessie fires off an energy orb. After hitting a target the orb bounces to the next target in range, hitting up to three enemies. Each bounce deals <damageDecayChain> less damage.

TID_MECHANIC_ULTI_DESC.EN: Jessie deploys a gun turret that automatically shoots at enemies. It's made of 100% recycled materials!

TID_SHAMAN_DESC.EN: Nita strikes her enemies with a thunderous shockwave. Her Super summons a massive bear to fight by her side!

TID_SHAMAN_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Nita sends forth a shockwave, damaging enemies caught in the tremor.

TID_SHAMAN_ULTI_DESC.EN: Nita summons the spirit of Big Baby Bear to hunt down her enemies.

TID_UNDERTAKER_DESC.EN: Mortis dashes forward with each swing of his shovel. As his Super attack, he sends a cloud of bats to damage enemies and heal himself!

TID_UNDERTAKER_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Mortis dashes forward with a sharp swing of his shovel, creating business opportunities for himself. When he has all three dashes ready, he'll gain a longer dash after a short delay.

TID_UNDERTAKER_ULTI_DESC.EN: Mortis calls forth a swarm of vampire bats that drain the health of enemy Brawlers while restoring his. Creepy!

TID_CROW_DESC.EN: This enigmatic creature just appeared in town one day. Nobody dares to ruffle his feathers - not anymore.

TID_CROW_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Crow throws a triple threat of daggers. Enemies hit by the poisoned blades will take damage over time and have all healing effects reduced for the duration.

TID_CROW_ULTI_DESC.EN: Crow takes to the skies, throwing a ring of poisoned daggers around him both on take-off and landing.

TID_DEAD_MARIACHI_DESC.EN: Poco fires damaging sound waves at enemies. His Super can heal both Poco himself and his teammates!

TID_DEAD_MARIACHI_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Poco strums his guitarr√≥n, sending forward bone-jarring sound waves. Enemies hit by the waves take damage.

TID_DEAD_MARIACHI_ULTI_DESC.EN: Poco heals himself and all friends he can reach with his uplifting melody. Does not affect enemies.

TID_BOW_DUDE_DESC.EN: Bo fires three explosive arrows toward his targets. His Super ability places a trio of hidden, explosive mines on the ground!

TID_BOW_DUDE_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Bo releases a trio of exploding arrows, tearing up enemies like an eagle's talons.

TID_BOW_DUDE_ULTI_DESC.EN: Bo hides explosive traps in the ground. When triggered by an enemy, the traps explode after a short delay, knocking back and damaging enemies.

TID_SNIPER_DESC.EN: Piper's sniper shots do more damage the farther they travel. Her Super drops grenades at her feet, while Piper herself leaps away!

TID_SNIPER_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Piper fires a sniper shot from the tip of her parasol. The shot gains more oompf the farther it flies!

TID_SNIPER_ULTI_DESC.EN: Piper hops away to avoid pushy suitors. She leaves them a lady's favor though: live grenades from her garter!

TID_MINIGUN_DUDE_DESC.EN: Pam shoots from the hip, peppering targets with shrapnel. Her Super is a healing turret that restores her and teammates' health!

TID_MINIGUN_DUDE_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Pam sprays a large area with bursts of scrap metal. Safety goggles advised!

TID_MINIGUN_DUDE_ULTI_DESC.EN: Pam's healing turret will fix up her and teammates who stay in its area of effect.

TID_BONE_THROWER_DESC.EN: There's nothing mini about this gunner! Handy with his massive machine gun, the Minigunner can mow down almost any number of bad guys. (Movement speed slow, immune to pushback)

TID_BONE_THROWER_WEAPON_DESC.EN: The Minigunner makes wielding this massive machine gun easy. He can even walk while firing it full auto!

TID_BONE_THROWER_ULTI_DESC.EN: Sometimes you get scratches and flesh wounds in a high-intensity firefight. The Bandage Dispenser helps keep your whole team in fighting shape!

TID_BLACK_HOLE_DESC.EN: What's in the cards for you? This mystic from a far land has come to read your fortune. It says simply: DEFEAT!

TID_BLACK_HOLE_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Tara flicks her wrist, snapping off three tarot cards that pierce through enemies. Quite a trick!

TID_BLACK_HOLE_ULTI_DESC.EN: Tara conjures up a mind-boggling gravity well! Enemies in the area of effect get pulled in, crashing together painfully hard.

TID_ROBOT_DESC.EN: Built to serve. Deputized to destroy.

TID_ROBOT_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Deputy Irons shoots an explosive rocket at extreme ranges with mechanical precision.

TID_ROBOT_ULTI_DESC.EN: When extreme measures are called for, Deputy Irons can rain down a barrage of rockets on the unruly crowd.

TID_GAME_MODE_0_DESC.EN: Collect Gems that pop out of the Gem Mine in the middle of the map. Or, just take them from fallen opponents! Hold ten gems for the duration of a countdown to win the game!

TID_GAME_MODE_2_DESC.EN: Protect your team's valuable safe, while trying to break open the enemy team's safe at the same time! Whichever team busts open the enemy safe first wins.\n\nIf time runs out, the team that caused more damage to the enemy team's safe is declared winner.

TID_GAME_MODE_3_DESC.EN: Collect Stars for your team by defeating players on the enemy team. Every time you defeat an enemy, the bounty on your head increases by one Star, up to seven Stars. Don't give them to the enemy!\n\nThe team that has more Stars when the clock runs out wins. In the case of a tie, the team holding the blue star wins.

TID_GAME_MODE_5_DESC.EN: Take the ball to the opposing team's goal to score! Match ends when one team scores two goals, or at full time.

TID_GAME_MODE_3_OG_DESC.EN: Collect Stars for your team by defeating players on the enemy team. Every time you defeat an enemy, the bounty on your head increases by one Star, up to seven Stars. Don't give them to the enemy!\n\nThe team that has more Stars when the clock runs out wins.

TID_GAME_MODE_11_DESC.EN:
Besiege and destroy the enemy's IKE assembly turret! Your team also has an IKE: feed it bolts, and it will assemble a powerful Siege Robot to fight for you. Bolts appear randomly around the middle of the map. Grab a bolt and hold it for a few seconds to feed it to your IKE.

There are up to three Sieges during each match. The team that has more bolts at the start of each Siege builds a Siege Robot. The more bolts, the stronger the robot.
Watch out, IKEs have powerful ballistic defenses - don't get too close to the enemy base without a Siege Robot to help you!

Star Powers are only available for Brawlers with Power Level 9. After unlocking <WCPP_BRAWLERS> Brawlers there will be a <WCPP_CHANCE>% chance that power points can be assigned to any Brawler. Once you have unlocked all rewards of a certain type, for example Rare Brawlers, the probability to get all other rewards will increase. Luck: In order to make the Brawl Box opening experience fairer, there is a luck system affecting the probability of Legendary Brawlers. With each draw that doesn't give you a new Brawler, your luck value is increased. Each time you get a new Brawler, your luck value decreases based on the rarity of the Brawler you got. When luck is high enough, you have a higher chance to get a Legendary Brawler, chance will not go higher than <MAX_LEGENDARY>%. TID_ROPE_DUDE_DESC.EN: Buzz is the lifeguard at Velocirapids. He constantly scans for folks in trouble he can throw his torpedo buoy to, but his throws are rather overenthusiastic.

TID_ROPE_DUDE_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Buzz blows on his lifeguard whistle, piercing nearby ears five times in an arc.

TID_ROPE_DUDE_ULTI_DESC.EN: Buzz throws out his torpedo buoy. If it hits an opponent or a wall, Buzz hauls himself over there, stunning nearby opponents where he lands.

TID_SPEC_ABI_ROPE_DUDE_1_DESC.EN: The minimum duration of Buzz's Super stun is increased by <c00cc00><VALUE1></c> seconds.

TID_SPEC_ABI_ROPE_DUDE_2_DESC.EN: Buzz's Super charging area is increased by <c00cc00><VALUE1>%</c>.

TID_ACCESSORY_ROPE_DUDE_WEAK_ULTI_DESC.EN: Instantly fills the Super meter, but the next Torpedo Throw doesn't stun opponents.

TID_ASSAULT_SHOTGUN_DESC.EN: Griff is the proprietor of Starr Park's gift shop. Business is bad, but he still throws coins away - from his employees' tip jar!

TID_ASSAULT_SHOTGUN_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Angry Griff pelts opponents with coins. He throws three salvos that spread out in a cone.

TID_ASSAULT_SHOTGUN_ULTI_DESC.EN: Griff throws a bunch of sharp-edged banknotes in a wide cone. Too valuable to just give away, they return to him, and may cause paper cuts twice to the same target. Opponents further away take more damage.

TID_SPEC_ABI_ASSAULT_SHOTGUN_1_DESC.EN: Furious Griff tosses coins faster, reducing the time for a full salvo by <c00cc00><VALUE1>%</c>.

TID_SPEC_ABI_ASSAULT_SHOTGUN_2_DESC.EN: Every <c00cc00><VALUE2></c> seconds, Griff regains up to <c00cc00><VALUE1>%</c> of his missing health.

TID_ACCESSORY_ASSAULT_SHOTGUN_BOMB_DESC.EN: Griff drops a firecracker-filled piggy bank that explodes after a short delay, destroying obstacles and dealing <c00cc00><VALUE1></c> damage to opponents within range.

TID_KNIGHT_DESC.EN: Ash easily gets furious about all the junk he has to clean up. Dealing or receiving blows, even more so. The Fury makes him faster and more dangerous, but eventually he cools down.

TID_KNIGHT_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Ash angrily smashes down with his broom. Get out of the way or you might bite the dust!

TID_KNIGHT_ULTI_DESC.EN: Robotic rats for cleaning up? That's right, they explode on contact, dealing damage to opponents and greatly increasing Ash's Rage level.

TID_SPEC_ABI_KNIGHT_1_DESC.EN: When hitting an opponent with his attack charges full, Ash gets even more angry. His Rage goes up by <c00cc00><VALUE1>%</c>.

TID_SPEC_ABI_KNIGHT_2_DESC.EN: Ash progressively gains up to <c00cc00><VALUE1>%</c> faster reload speed, equal to how enraged he's become.

TID_ACCESSORY_KNIGHT_HEAL_DESC.EN: Though furious, Ash has to collect himself. A full Rage meter will recover <c00cc00><VALUE1></c> health when this gadget is popped - less Rage, less recovery.

TID_MECHA_DUDE_DESC.EN: Meg has a basic form and an advanced form where she hops inside her trusted Mecha suit. The suit gradually loses health, returning Meg to her basic form when the Mecha suit is destroyed.

TID_MECHA_DUDE_WEAPON_DESC.EN: Meg fires a short burst from her blaster that pokes at her enemies' patience.

TID_MECHA_DUDE_ULTI_DESC.EN: Meg jumps into her Mecha suit for some colossal carnage!

TID_MECHA_DUDE_BIG_WEAPON_DESC.EN: A strong barrage of bullets that leaves nothing to chance. It's the quickest way to make crowds disperse!

TID_MECHA_DUDE_BIG_ULTI_DESC.EN: The Mecha swings a formidable forearm that enemies will see and feel.

TID_SPEC_ABI_MECHA_DUDE_1_DESC.EN: Meg is protected by a <c00cc00><VALUE1>%</c> shield for <c00cc00><VALUE2></c> seconds when her Mecha is destroyed.

TID_SPEC_ABI_MECHA_DUDE_2_DESC.EN: Upon expiring, the Mecha suit explodes, dealing <c00cc00><VALUE1></c> damage to nearby opponents and pushing them away.

TID_ACCESSORY_MECHA_DUDE_HEAL_DESC.EN: Heal the Mecha by <c00cc00><VALUE1></c> health per second for <c00cc00><VALUE2></c> seconds.
